title: For Sale:  vintage Iver Johnson Champion single shot break action 28 gauge shotgun
postcontent:
The Iver Johnson "Champion" was first made in 1880.  The Champion Model 36 was made from 1909 to 1922. Its name was changed to Champion Single Barrel in 1923. They were made until approximately 1978. This version had blued steel barrels, ejectors, a case hardened receiver and walnut stock.
This example appears to have a 28" barrel; finish about 50%, some surface rust but nothing major, it would probably clean up with steel wool and oil and with some touchup bluing may appear good as new.  Some scratches on front of barrel also, but no rust in that area.  Wood is ready for a refinish.  Plastic Iver Johnson buttpad.  Hammer is stiff, the whole gun could use a stripdown, scrub, and full lube job, but I’m confident it’ll shoot like the day it was new with some oil.  If you've ever handled and shot single shot break open shotguns like this, they just have a wonderful balance and pointability and are perfect for squirrel and bird hunting.  I also have a couple boxes of vintage 28 gauge shotshells, it looks like 2 boxes of #6 shot and a third box of #4 shot that may only be partially full.
More pics available upon request, I tried to take as many pictures as possible especially of the blemish areas, I'm not trying to waste anyone's time.  $100.  Buyer must comply with all applicable laws.  NO TRADES - CASH ONLY - IN TOWN/LOCAL/FACE TO FACE SALES ONLY - NO SHIPPING.I can meet at your choice of local gun store or parking lot of local law enforcement agency for inspection of firearm.
